%20healthcare%20company%20Corizon%20Health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYesterday%2C%20the%20senator%20sent%20a%20sharply%20worded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.warren.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2F2024.01.31%2520Letter%2520to%2520U.S.%2520Trustee%2520re%2520Corizon%2520Bankrupcy.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eletter%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice's%20U.S.%20Trustee%20Program%20and%20one%20of%20its%20regional%20offices%20in%20Texas%20encouraging%20officials%20to%20oppose%20the%20bankruptcy%20plan%20and%20join%20a%20motion%20to%20dismiss%20the%20case%20%E2%80%94%20and%20blasting%20the%20company%20for%20claiming%20not%20to%20know%20its%20own%20ownership%20structure.%20Warren%20asked%20the%20officials%20to%20respond%20to%20her%20requests%20by%20February%2014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCorizon%20is%20misusing%20the%20bankruptcy%20system%20to%20evade%20accountability%20and%20block%20the%20company's%20victims%20and%20their%20families%20from%20obtaining%20justice%2C%26quot%3B%20Warren%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThe%20U.S.%20Trustee's%20office%20has%20acted%20powerfully%20to%20protect%20the%20rights%20of%20victims%20harmed%20by%20corporations%20that%20seek%20to%20escape%20liability.%20Likewise%2C%20it%20should%20stand%20up%20to%20Corizon's%20abusive%20tactics%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20our%20bankruptcy%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarren%20applauded%20the%20US%20Trustee%20Program%2C%20which%20oversees%20the%20federal%20bankruptcy%20system%2C%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-deal-settlement-threatened-issues-objections-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emaking%20a%20rare%20decision%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%20to%20file%20an%20objection%20in%20court%20to%20Corizon's%20bankruptcy%20plan.%20The%20move%20came%20after%20a%20Business%20Insider%20series%20exposing%20the%20company's%20attempts%20to%20shed%20responsibility%20for%20hundreds%20of%20lawsuits%20alleging%20medical%20neglect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-yescare-texas-two-step-law-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereporting%20revealed%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Corizon%20had%20engaged%20in%20a%20controversial%20legal%20maneuver%20called%20the%20Texas%20Two-Step%2C%20which%20involved%20splitting%20into%20two%20companies.%20One%20company%2C%20YesCare%2C%20got%20all%20of%20Corizon's%20active%20corrections%20contracts%20while%20the%20other%20company%2C%20Tehum%20Care%20Services%2C%20was%20saddled%20with%20the%20company's%20liabilities%20and%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy.%20The%20maneuver%2C%20Warren%20wrote%2C%20was%20done%20%26quot%3Bexplicitly%20to%20evade%20its%20liabilities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorizon's%20current%20bankruptcy%20plan%2C%20she%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3Bwill%20deny%20Corizon's%20creditors%2C%20including%20incarcerated%20individuals%2C%20adequate%20restitution%20for%20the%20company's%20serious%20harms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJason%20Brookner%2C%20an%20attorney%20representing%20Tehum%2C%20declined%20to%20comment%2C%20saying%20the%20company%20had%20not%20received%20the%20letter.%20Representatives%20for%20YesCare%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%2C%20the%20US%20Trustee%20intervened%20in%20the%20case%2C%20pushing%20for%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20committee%20to%20represent%20the%20hundreds%20of%20current%20and%20former%20incarcerated%20patients%20who%20allege%20they%20were%20harmed%20under%20Corizon's%20care.%20Those%20plaintiffs%20had%20been%20allocated%20a%20disproportionately%20small%20share%20of%20the%20initial%20proposed%20settlement.%20Earlier%20this%20month%2C%20that%20committee%20moved%20to%20dismiss%20the%20bankruptcy%2C%20citing%20%26quot%3Ba%20bad%20faith%20settlement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20encourage%20you%20to%20promptly%20review%20the%20motion%20and%20join%20it%20if%20you%20find%20the%20motion%20meritorious%2C%26quot%3B%20Warren%20wrote%20to%20the%20US%20Trustee%20officials.%20Warren%20said%20she%20believed%20the%20motion%20%26quot%3Bargues%20persuasively%20that%20bankruptcy%20is%20not%20the%20appropriate%20venue%20for%20dealing%20with%20Corizon's%20harms%2C%20and%20that%20the%20purpose%20of%20the%20bankruptcy%20is%20not%20to%20fairly%20compensate%20all%20creditors%20but%20to%20transfer%20value%20from%20victims%20to%20investors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmma%20Dulaney%2C%20press%20secretary%20for%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%2C%20which%20oversees%20the%20US%20Trustee%20Program%2C%20confirmed%20receipt%20of%20the%20letter%20but%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20time%20Warren%20has%20weighed%20in%20on%20the%20Corizon%20bankruptcy.%20In%20October%2C%20she%20joined%20eight%20other%20Senators%2C%20including%20Senate%20Judiciary%20Chair%20Dick%20Durbin%2C%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenator-warren-oversight-letter-on-corizon-tehum-yescare-bankruptcy-deal-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esending%20a%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Tehum%20and%20YesCare%20demanding%20answers%20about%20the%20companies'%20ownership%20and%20corporate%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarren%20also%20encouraged%20the%20US%20Trustee%20to%20investigate%20Corizon's%20transfer%20of%20significant%20assets%20to%20YesCare%20or%20any%20entities%20affiliated%20with%20Corizon's%20owners.%20Under%20federal%20bankruptcy%20law%2C%20a%20trustee%20can%20reverse%20asset%20sales%20or%20transfers%20that%20took%20place%20within%20two%20years%20of%20a%20bankruptcy%20filing%20if%20certain%20conditions%20are%20met%2C%20Warren%20wrote%2C%20saying%20Corizon's%20transfers%20%26quot%3Bwarrant%20serious%20examination.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20in%20all%2C%20Corizon%20transferred%20at%20least%20%24200%20million%20to%20YesCare%20and%20to%20entities%20affiliated%20with%20its%20private%20equity%20owner%20prior%20to%20declaring%20bankruptcy%2C%26quot%3B%20Warren%20wrote%20in%20yesterday's%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20asked%20the%20US%20Trustee%20to%20continue%20digging%20into%20Corizon's%20owners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20identity%20of%20other%20investors%20in%20the%20private%20equity%20firm%20that%20acquired%20Corizon%20in%20December%202021%20is%20still%20not%20publicly%20known%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3Bas%20is%20whether%20they%20or%20their%20affiliated%20companies%20received%20assets%20prior%20to%20the%20bankruptcy%20filing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarren%20and%20her%20Senate%20colleagues%20sought%20answers%20to%20that%20question%20in%20their%20first%20letter%2C%20but%20she%20said%20the%20companies%20failed%20to%20provide%20details%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.warren.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2F2023.11.15%2520Tehum%2520Response%2520to%2520Senate%2520Letter%2520%5BRedacted%5D.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etheir%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.warren.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2F2023.11.15%2520YesCare%2520Response%2520to%2520Senate%2520Letter%2520%5BRedacted%5D.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eresponses%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Warren%20made%20the%20companies'%20responses%20public%20this%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Warren%20noted%20that%20YesCare%20said%2C%20in%20its%20response%20signed%20by%20counsel%20Raphael%20Prober%2C%20that%20it%20doesn't%20know%20its%20ownership%20structure.%20%26quot%3BYesCare%20is%20wholly%20owned%20by%20YesCare%20Holdings%2C%20LLC%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20response%20reads.%20%26quot%3BThe%20ownership%20structure%20of%20YesCare%20Holdings%2C%20LLC%20is%20not%20information%20that%20is%20publicly%20available%20or%20known%20to%20YesCare.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20Warren%20said%2C%20the%20US%20Trus