ns-satisfied-number-friends-closeness-friendships.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGallup%20survey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20which%20just%202%25%20of%20Americans%20said%20they%20had%20no%20close%20friends%20%E2%80%94%20and%2018-%20to%2029-year-olds%20reported%20having%20a%20mean%20of%208.9%20friends%2C%20which%20was%20higher%20than%20in%20other%20age%20cohorts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20in%20the%20prime%20time%20to%20forge%20lasting%20relationships%2C%20they're%20finding%20it%20extremely%20difficult%20to%20make%20friends.%20It's%20not%20as%20if%20young%20people%20don't%20want%20connection%20%E2%80%94%20the%20popularity%20of%20Moses'%20events%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-loneliness-spends-money-to-make-friends-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eamounts%20of%20money%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20willing%20to%20spend%20on%20social%20activities%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20proof%20that%20people%20still%20want%20to%20cultivate%20social%20circles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20why%20are%20so%20many%20floundering%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20reasons%20for%20our%20shrinking%20social%20circles%20is%20the%20loss%20of%20fringe%20friends%20%E2%80%94%20casual%20friends%20that%20you%20enjoy%20seeing%20occasionally.%20These%20are%20the%20people%20you%20see%20only%20at%20parties%20but%20are%20always%20happy%20to%20chat%20with.%20The%20people%20who%20you%20see%20at%20the%20local%20watering%20hole%20every%20so%20often%2C%20and%20maybe%20challenge%20to%20a%20game%20of%20darts.%20The%20people%20who%20ended%20up%20in%20your%20orbit%20by%20proximity%20%E2%80%94%20the%20ones%20who%20rode%20the%20subway%20to%20work%20with%20you%20at%20the%20same%20time%20every%20day%20or%20waited%20next%20to%20you%20for%20their%20morning%20coffee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHave%20you%20seen%20any%20of%20those%20people%20in%20recent%20years%3F%20If%20you're%20like%20me%2C%20the%20answer%20is%20probably%20not.%20I%20caught%20a%20glimpse%20of%20one%20of%20my%20fringe%20friends%20months%20ago%20on%20the%20streets%20of%20Brooklyn%20and%20realized%20how%20long%20it%20had%20been%20since%20I%20saw%20them.%20When%20I%20went%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20interview%20them%20for%20this%20story%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20didn't%20even%20have%20their%20number%3B%20we%20chatted%20a%20bit%20on%20Instagram%2C%20and%2C%20like%20the%20arc%20of%20many%20of%20these%20friendships%2C%20our%20conversation%20ended%20up%20fizzling%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20relationships%20might%20seem%20trivial%20or%20inconsequential%2C%20but%20experts%20and%20research%20indicate%20that%20fringe%20friends%20are%20vital.%20These%20loose%20connections%20are%20the%20people%20who%20might%20introduce%20you%20to%20a%20hobby%2C%20invite%20you%20to%20a%20book%20club%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-dating-trend-online-apps-friends-romantic-partners-relationships-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eeven%20end%20up%20becoming%20your%20spouse%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20now%20these%20fringe%20friend%20groups%20are%20disappearing%2C%20and%20we're%20all%20worse%20off%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20we%20lose%20without%20fringe%20friends%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20few%20things%20more%20important%20in%20people's%20lives%20than%20their%20friendships.%20In%20fact%2C%20in%20a%202023%20survey%20by%20the%20Pew%20Research%20Center%2C%20many%20Americans%20said%20that%20close%20friendships%20were%20more%20necessary%20for%20a%20complete%20life%20than%20other%20traditional%20forms%20of%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BClose%20friendships%20make%20for%20a%20more-fulfilling%20life%20in%20people's%20minds%20than%20necessarily%20being%20married%20or%20having%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20Juliana%20Horowitz%2C%20an%20associate%20director%20of%20research%20at%20Pew%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20with%20that%20knowledge%2C%20Americans%20are%20struggling%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20these%20connections.%20In%20a%201990%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F10891%2Famericans-satisfied-number-friends-closeness-friendships.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGallup%20survey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%203%25%20of%20Americans%20said%20that%20they%20had%20no%20close%20friends.%20By%20contrast%2C%20the%20American%20Survey%20Center's%202021%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americansurveycenter.org%2Fresearch%2Fthe-state-of-american-friendship-change-challenges-and-loss%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAmerican%20Perspectives%20Survey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20number%20had%20risen%20to%2012%25.%20One-third%20of%20Americans%20in%201990%20said%20they%20had%2010%20or%20more%20close%20friends%2C%20while%20just%2013%25%20said%20the%20same%20in%202021.%20And%20while%20there's%20the%20old%20refrain%20about%20quality%20over%20quantity%2C%20Americans%20become%20more%20satisfied%20with%20the%20number%20of%20friends%20they%20have%20as%20that%20number%20increases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FJwPED%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Number%20of%20close%20friends%20by%20age%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22285%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Cox%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Survey%20Center%20on%20American%20Life%20at%20the%20American%20Enterprise%20Institute%2C%20told%20me%20the%20%26quot%3Bnotion%20that%20you%20can%20have%20one%20or%20two%20close%20friends%2C%20and%20that's%20enough%20to%20get%20you%20through%20things%2C%20is%20just%20not%20borne%20out%20by%20the%20data.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20find%20that%20even%20for%20close%20friends%2C%20the%20more%20you%20have%2C%20the%20better%20you%20do%20on%20a%20variety%20of%20measures%2C%20whether%20it's%20loneliness%2C%20whether%20it's%20physical%20health%2C%20life%20satisfaction%20%E2%80%94%20all%20these%20things%20are%20higher%20when%20you%20hit%20four%20or%20five%20or%20six%20friends.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20maintaining%20a%20sizable%2C%20emotionally%20connected%20group%20is%20important%2C%20the%20more%20run-of-the-mill%20social%20interactions%20are%20equally%20critical%2C%20Cox%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20some%20ways%2C%20these%20weak%20social%20ties%20are%20even%20more%20important%20than%20our%20intimate%20friendships%20and%20relationships%20that%20we%20have%20because%20they%20connect%20us%20to%20a%20wider%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Cox%20said.%20People%20tend%20to%20engage%20in%20what's%20called%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2006%2F12%2F10%2Fmagazine%2F10Section2a.t-4.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehomophily%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Cox%20said%2C%20which%20is%20when%20you%20cluster%20%E2%80%94%20romantically%20or%20platonically%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0with%20people%20like%20you%2C%20whether%20that's%20racially%2C%20religiously%2C%20or%20politically.%20More-distant%20relationships%20are%20so%20important%20because%20they're%20often%20the%20people%20who%20don't%20share%20those%20same%20kinds%20of%20characteristics%20and%20attributes%2C%20Cox%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20able%20to%20share%20with%20us%20experiences%20that%20are%20very%20different%20or%20provide%20us%20with%20information%20we%20may%20not%20otherwise%20have%20access%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20Cox%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETalking%20to%20Cox%2C%20I%20started%20to%20think%20about%20my%20local%20bodega%20buddy.%20During%20the%20darkest%20days%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20I'd%20go%20%E2%80%94%20double-masked%20%E2%80%94%20to%20the%20bodega%20a%20few%20blocks%20away%20once%20a%20week.%20I%20was%20a%20remote%20worker%3B%20he%20was%20a%20student%20sent%20online%20who%20worked%20nights%20at%20the%20store.%20Having%20someone%20who%20knew%20me%20and%20was%20ready%20to%20chat%20as%20he%20fired%20up%20my%20regular%20order%20brought%20much-needed%20lightness%20during%20a%20dark%20time.%20We%20even%20established%20our%20own%20barter%20system%3A%20I'd%20bring%20him%20whatever%20pandemic%20baking%20I'd%20made%20that%20week%2C%20and%20in%20return%2C%20he'd%20let%20me%20pick%20out%20a%20snack.%20That's%20not%20a%20relationship%20I%20could've%20cultivated%20while%20ordering%20delivery%20from%20my%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELosing%20fringe%20acquaintances%20means%20losing%20people%20who%20push%20you%20out%20of%20your%20comfort%20zone%20or%20who%20might%20shape%20you%20in%20unexpected%20ways.%20They%20can%20be%20critical%20for%20you%20in%20finding%20a%20new%20job%2C%20a%20new%20way%20of%20thinking%2C%20or%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-dating-trend-online-apps-friends-romantic-partners-relationships-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20romantic%20partner%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20also%20lose%20something%20beyond%20a%20prospective%20friend%20or%20partner%20when%20distant%20ties%20disappear%2C%20as%20Cox%20told%20me%3A%20We%20also%20become%20less%20connected%20to%20our%20neighborhoods%2C%20communities%2C%20and%20other%20societal%20institutions.%20That's%20bad%20news%20for%20an%20increasingly%20lonely%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EShriveling%20social%20circles%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20pandemic%20created%20an%20acute%20fringe-friend%20crisis%2C%20the%20loss%20of%20these%20outlying%20social%20systems%20has%20been%20brewing%20for%20decades.%20According%20to%20the%20experts%20I%20talked%20to%2C%20there%20are%20two%20big%20reasons%20for%20the%20shift%3A%20We've%20shrunk%20the%20physical%20spaces%20in%20which%20we%20interact%20with%20people%2C%20and%20we've%20shrunk%20the%20emotional%20space%20to%20trust%20the%20people%20with%20whom%20we%20do%20interact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20no%20secret%20that%20Americans%2C%20and%20younger%20people%20especially%2C%20are%20spending%20less%20time%20with%20other%20humans.%20The%20amount%20of%20time%20spent%20alone%20has%20increased%20by%20over%205%25%20from%202003%20to%202019%2C%20research%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.philadelphiafed.org%2Fthe-economy%2Fmacroeconomics%2Fhow-time-spent-alone-in-the-us-has-changed-over-the-past-two-decades-and-implications-for-well-being%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EFederal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20Philadelphia%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20found.%20And%2C%20come%20the%20pandemic%20in%202020%2C%20people%20were%20spending%20a%20little%20over%20half%20their%20free%20time%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20felt%20physically%20and%20psychologically%20dangerous%20to%20be%20in%20spaces%20with%20other%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Danielle%20Bayard%20Jackson%2C%20a%20friendship%20coach%20and%20educator%2C%20told%20me.%20It's%20been%20hard%20for%20many%20people%20to%20get%20comfortable%20returning%20to%20spaces%2C%20especially%20as%20the%20risk%20of%20illness%20lingers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FgLrDI%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22How%20Americans%20spend%20their%20time%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20pandemic%20wasn't%20the%20start%20of%20this%20hangout%20crisis.%20For%20years%2C%20third%20spaces%20%E2%80%94%20places%20that%20aren't%20your%20home%20or%20office%20but%20a%20casual%2C%20free%20hangout%20spot%20%E2%80%94%20have%20been%20dwindling.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-epidemic-decline-in-third-places-friends-parks-community-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecasual%20places%20to%20hang%20out%20with%20people%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20libraries%2C%20parks%2C%20or%20coffee%20shops%2C%20are%20disappearing.%20Instead%2C%20everything%20has%20to%20be%20paid%20for%20and%20intentional.%20The%20lack%20of%20places%20to%20interact%20with%20people%20from%20different%20walks%20of%20life%20even%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-wants-to-go-in-office-bosses-dont-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eyoung%20people%20yearning%20for%20less%20time%20working%20remotely%20and%20more%20time%20in%20the%20once%20dreaded%20office%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20places%20that%20you'd%20normally%20meet%20fringe%20friends%2C%20which%20would%20eventually%20develop%20into%20a%20proper%20friend%2C%20they%20don't%20exist%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20Moses%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FtICjL%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Weekday%20socializing%20and%20communicating%20%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%20that%20casual%20hangout%20spaces%20are%20falling%20by%20the%20wayside%2C%20Cox%20said%2C%20membership%20in%20institutions%20that%20might%20provide%20social%20frameworks%20and%20structures%20%E2%80%94%20places%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flabor-union-membership-fell-lowest-rate-record-2022-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eunions%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F341963%2Fchurch-membership-falls-below-majority-first-time.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereligious%20communities%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20the%20school%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC6545986%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPTA%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20has%20also%20declined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20these%20relationships%20were%20forged%20through%20joint%20membership%20in%20these%20organizations%2C%26quot%3B%20Cox%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20fewer%20of%20us%20are%20doing%20that%2C%20and%20particularly%20fewer%20men%20are%20doing%20that%2C%20we're%20limiting%20the%20opportunity%20to%20develop%20strong%2C%20enduring%20friendships%2C%20which%20are%20absolutely%20critical.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20online%20spaces%20where%20people%20once%20found%20new%20friends%20or%20organized%20their%20social%20lives%20have%20started%20to%20lose%20what%20little%20connective%20power%20they%20had.%20Long%20gone%20are%20the%20days%20that%20you%20might%20log%20on%20to%20Facebook%2C%20see%20some%20personal%20updates%2C%20and%20then%20peruse%20event%20invitations%20from%20people%20you%20were%20tenuously%20connected%20to.%20Social%20media%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-media-splintering-new-less-toxic-era-meta-bluesky-twitter-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebecome%20decentralized%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20public%20feeds%20bogged%20down%20by%20impersonal%2C%20professional%20content%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-media-dead-instagram-tiktok-bereal-replaced-group-chats-messaging-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereal%20socializing%20happens%20in%20group%20DMs%20or%20messaging%20apps%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20people%20chat%20with%20a%20tight%20circle%20of%20preexisting%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvan%20Paul%20Cudworth%2C%20a%20party%20coach%2C%20a%20role%20that%20he%20said%20he%20always%20took%20on%20socially%20but%20made%20into%20a%20job%20in%202021%20to%20help%20people%20craft%20healthier%20social%20lives%2C%20told%20me%20that%20one%20of%20his%20most%20powerful%20friend%20experiences%20came%20after%20he%20moved%20to%20New%20York%20in%20his%20early%2020s%20and%20started%20going%20to%20nightclubs.%20After%20he%20saw%20the%20same%20handful%20of%20people%20out%20and%20about%2C%20they%20decided%20to%20create%20a%20Facebook%20group%20to%20coordinate%20and%20sell%20tickets%20to%20each%20other%20for%20various%20events.%20The%20group%20slowly%20morphed%20into%20something%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEventually%2C%20we%20started%20all%20going%20to%20the%20same%20shows%20together%2C%20and%20then%20we%20created%20a%20logo%20and%20people%20got%20tattoos%20of%20the%20logo%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20all%20these%20fringe%20people%2C%20but%20a%20couple%20hundred%20of%20us%20would%20all%20see%20each%20other%20out%20at%20these%20same%20events.%26quot%3B%20It%20was%20%26quot%3Bso%20cool%26quot%3B%20to%20see%20this%20community%20of%20all%20different%20types%20of%20people%20grow%2C%20Cudworth%20said%2C%20but%20nowadays%2C%20he%20isn't%20sure%20it%20could%20be%20replicated%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20feel%20a%20lot%20of%20that%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20physical%20and%20cyberspaces%20where%20we%20interact%20have%20become%20harder%20to%20find%2C%20so%20too%20has%20Americans'%20emotional%20willingness%20to%20open%20themselves%20up%20to%20new%20people%20and%20experiences.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2019%2F07%2F22%2Fkey-findings-about-americans-declining-trust-in-government-and-each-other%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPew%20Research%20Center%20report%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%202019%2C%2064%25%20of%20adults%20said%20they%20believed%20that%20Americans'%20trust%20in%20each%20other%20had%20been%20shrinking.%20In%202020%2C%2046%25%20of%20respondents%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2020%2F04%2F06%2Fthe-state-of-americans-trust-in-each-other-amid-the-covid-19-pandemic%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPew%20survey%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20pandemic%20said%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BMost%20people%20can't%20be%20trusted.%26quot%3B%20Younger%20Americans%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20were%20much%20less%20trusting%20than%20their%20older%20counterparts%3B%20just%2034%25%20of%20Americans%20ages%2018%20to%2029%20said%20that%20most%20people%20could%20be%20trusted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20don't%20introduce%20themselves%20to%20their%20neighbors.%20Trust%20allows%20vulnerability%2C%20and%20you%20need%20vulnerability%20to%20create%20friendships%2C%26quot%3B%20Anna%20Goldfarb%2C%20the%20author%20of%20the%20upcoming%20book%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D8d1b311cac4bb229518bd16da188b60b46af82e4649131effff659d900d2908c%26postID%3D65a6f083a62cdd3ed803babc%26postSlug%3Ddeath-casual-fringe-friendships-gen-z-sad-jobs-alone-2024-2%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fbookshop.org%252Fp%252Fbooks%252Fmodern-friendship-how-to-nurture-our-most-valued-connections-anna-goldfarb%252F20322383%253Fean%253D9781649632081%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EModern%20Friendship%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20writer%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fannagoldfarb.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESubstack%20newsletter%20on%20friendship%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToo%20many%20of%20us%20are%20no%20longer%20exchanging%20a%20few%20words%20with%20the%20person%20in%20the%20elevator%2C%20cracking%20a%20few%20jokes%20with%20the%20coworker%20at%20an%20after-office%20happy%20hour%2C%20or%20asking%20the%20guy%20at%20the%20bodega%20how%20his%20week's%20been%20going.%20Part%20of%20that%20might%20be%20rooted%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20younger%20people%20aren't%20able%20to%20put%20down%20roots%20in%20the%20same%20way%20as%20their%20older%20peers%2C%20jumping%20from%20rental%20to%20rental%20or%20job%20to%20job%2C%20and%20can%20buy%20only%20homes%20far%20away%20from%20their%20urban%20hubs.%20What's%20the%20point%20in%20saying%20hi%20if%20you're%20going%20to%20change%20bodegas%20or%20coworking%20spaces%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20months%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20Gen%20Zers%20chasing%20cheap%20rent%2C%20I%20ended%20up%20moving%20away%20from%20my%20bodega%20buddy.%20On%20the%20occasions%20I've%20been%20back%2C%20I've%20missed%20him%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20my%20schedule%20has%20become%20misaligned%20or%20he's%20back%20at%20school%20full%20time%2C%20or%20he's%20moved%20on%20to%20another%20bodega.%20Whatever%20the%20reason%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20I'll%20see%20him%20again.%20That's%20another%20fringe%20acquaintance%20gone%2C%20vanished%20into%20the%20ether%20by%20the%20socioeconomic%20realities%20that%20weigh%20on%20our%20connections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20we%20do%20make%20plans%20or%20an%20attempt%20to%20cement%20the%20ties%20that%20bind%20us%2C%20Cudworth%20told%20me%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bradical%20individualism%26quot%3B%20stoked%20by%20the%20pandemic%20had%20made%20it%20more%20acceptable%20to%20cancel%20plans%20and%20just%20sit%20alone.%20While%20taking%20care%20of%20one's%20mental%20health%20is%20good%20%E2%80%94%20as%20Cudworth%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20get%20it%3B%20people%20deserve%20their%20peace%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20we%20are%20ultimately%20%26quot%3Ba%20society%20that%20relies%20on%20a%20culture%20of%20integrity%20and%20showing%20up%20and%20doing%20the%20thing%20that%20maybe%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20do%2C%20but%20you're%20going%20to%20love%20that%20you%20did%20it%20by%20showing%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGlimmers%20of%20hope%20for%20Gen%20Z%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decline%20in%20fringe%20friends%20has%20also%20created%20a%20generational%20divide%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20who's%20doing%20well%20socially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOlder%20Americans%20are%20more%20likely%20than%20younger%20Americans%20to%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20close%20friends%2C%26quot%3B%20Pew's%20Horowitz%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20as%20they%20have%20fewer%20close%20friends%2C%20younger%20Americans%20rely%20on%20those%20relationships.%20The%20American%20Perspectives%20Survey%20found%20younger%20Americans%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20lean%20on%20a%20friend%20when%20dealing%20with%20personal%20problems%20but%20were%20also%20more%20likely%20to%20say%20that%20they'd%20lost%20touch%20with%20most%20or%20a%20few%20of%20their%20friends%20in%20the%2012%20months%20before%20the%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Jackson%2C%20the%20friendship%20coach%20and%20educator%2C%20Gen%20Z%20is%20also%20the%20generation%20most%20actively%20trying%20to%20buck%20this%20trend.%20She%20said%20that%20she'd%20been%20hearing%20more%20of%20a%20desire%20for%20friend%20groups%20from%20people%20in%20their%20mid-20s.%20People%20are%20pointing%20to%20social-media%20trends%20where%20groups%20show%20off%20silly%20conversations%20in%20their%20group%20chats%2C%20or%20inside-joke%20archetypes%20in%20their%20friend%20groups%2C%20and%20saying%20that's%20what%20they%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20real%20solution%20to%20the%20loss%20of%20fringe%20friends.%20They%20might%20not%20exist%20in%20the%20way%20they%20did%20before%20the%20pandemic%20ever%20again.%20It%20doesn't%20help%20that%2C%20as%20Goldfarb%20said%2C%20it's%20never%20been%20harder%20to%20form%20lasting%20friendships.%20But%20there%20are%20glimmers%20of%20hope%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0Moses'%20sold-out%20events%2C%20for%20one%2C%20and%20an%20increased%20desire%20for%20third%20places%20to%20hang%20out%20in%20for%20free%20and%20for%20as%20long%20as%20you%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20might%20be%20cynical%20and%20sad%2C%20but%20I%20do%20think%20that%20we're%20just%20going%20to%20see%20people%20get%20maybe%20just%20more%20online%2C%20more%20lonelier%2C%26quot%3B%20Moses%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20if%20you%20want%20to%20make%20new%20friends%2C%20I%20think%20there's%20going%20to%20be%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I've%20seen%20it%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20just%20going%20to%20be%20heaps%20and%20heaps%20of%20new%20initiatives%20to%20make%20new%20friends.%20It's%20just%20a%20matter%20of%20if%20you%20actually%20want%20to%20go.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjuliana-kaplan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJuliana%20Kaplan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20senior%20labor%20and%20inequality%20reporter%20on%20Insider's%20economy%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeath-casual-fringe-friendships-gen-z-sad-jobs-alone-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706791836000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b3cefd43bb77284ba0bfb9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeath-casual-fringe-friendships-gen-z-sad-jobs-alone-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22People%2C%20especially%20Gen%20Zers%2C%20aren't%20forming%20as%20many%20casual%20%26quot%3Bfringe%20friendships.%26quot%3B%20This%20is%20leaving%20us%20all%20sadder%2C%20angrier%2C%20and%20lonely.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeath-casual-fringe-friendships-gen-z-sad-jobs-alone-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fireworks%20and%20egg%20throwing%20at%20EU%20farmer%20protest%20in%20Brussels%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706791398000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F1376A%2Fproduction%2F_132522797_p0h8dvd3.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68168498%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Farmers%20from%20across%20the%20EU%20converge%20demand%20fewer%20regulations%20as%20European%20leaders%20meet%20for%20summit.%22%2C%22author