iving%20meant%20flying%20600%20miles%20to%20my%20mom%20every%203%20weeks.%20It%20showed%20me%20family%20bonds%20transcend%20all.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20packing%20suitcase.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b7cc5cac2de4f17ee56a8b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETiffany%20Drummond%20(not%20pictured)%20flew%20from%20New%20York%20to%20North%20Carolina%20every%20three%20weeks%20while%20caregiving%20for%20her%20mother.%3Cp%3EAdene%20Sanchez%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20mom%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20stage%20III%20endometrial%20cancer%20in%202014.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20I%20was%20living%20almost%20600%20miles%20away%2C%20but%20wanted%20to%20be%20her%20caregiver.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20employer%20made%20accommodations%20so%20that%20I%20could%20fly%20to%20her%20side%20every%20three%20weeks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20typical%20workday%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202014.%20Confined%20to%20my%20desk%20in%20gray-toned%20cubicle%20purgatory%2C%20I%20was%20sifting%20through%20uninspiring%20emails%20and%20conjuring%20excuses%20to%20avoid%20scheduled%20meetings.%20Though%20I%20cannot%20remember%20the%20exact%20October%20day%2C%20the%20phone%20call%20I%20received%20is%20one%20I%20will%20never%20forget.%20It%20was%20the%20day%20an%20ambulance%20rushed%20my%20mother%20to%20the%20hospital%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20day%20%26quot%3Bcancer%26quot%3B%20became%20a%20routine%20topic%20of%20conversation%20in%20our%20household.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20numerous%20blood%20draws%2C%20biopsies%2C%20and%20MRIs%2C%20the%20results%20were%20crystal%20clear%3A%20my%20mother%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-endometrial-cancer-doctor-easy-to-miss-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estage%20III%20endometrial%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20will%20not%20get%20into%20the%20complexity%20of%20staging%2C%20but%20knowing%20that%20there%20are%20only%20four%20stages%20of%20this%20specific%20type%20of%20cancer%20was%20a%20dose%20of%20reality%20that%20I%20kept%20to%20myself%20as%20long%20as%20possible.%20I%20remember%20my%20father%20asking%20me%20outside%20the%20hospital%20room%20to%20be%20honest%2C%20and%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20good.%26quot%3B%20But%20I%20also%20knew%20my%20mother%2C%20and%20anyone%20who%20knew%20her%20as%20I%20did%20understood%20she%20would%20not%20be%20going%20down%20without%20a%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20wanted%20to%20be%20my%20mother's%20caregiver%20but%20lived%20600%20miles%20away%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20care%20team%20developed%20a%20treatment%20plan%20that%20included%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeing-organized-helped-me-through-my-cancer-diagnosis-and-treatment-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emonthly%20rounds%20of%20chemotherapy%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20radiation.%20My%20family%20agreed%20I%20was%20the%20obvious%20choice%20to%20accompany%20my%20mother%20to%20most%20of%20her%20appointments%2C%20though%20my%20siblings%20and%20other%20family%20members%20scheduled%20time%20to%20be%20there%20without%20hesitation.%20Those%20uninspiring%20emails%20and%20scheduled%20meetings%20were%20part%20of%20my%20role%20as%20a%20clinical%20hematology%20and%20oncology%20research%20professional.%20Working%20in%20this%20space%20allowed%20me%20the%20opportunity%20to%20become%20knowledgeable%20not%20just%20about%20cancer%20but%20many%20of%20the%20medical%20terms%20and%20jargon%20that%20were%20sure%20to%20be%20thrown%20around%20during%20her%20cancer%20journey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22621%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author's%20mother%20when%20she%20was%20younger.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b7ca876c8f0a134f7ab4da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22621%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETiffany%20Drummond's%20mother%20when%20she%20was%20younger.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20believe%20parents%20have%20children%20for%20many%20reasons%2C%20one%20being%20that%20their%20children%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaregiver-returning-to-workforce-advice-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecare%20for%20them%20in%20old%20age%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20sickness.%20Though%20I%20was%20willing%20and%20able%20to%20fulfill%20this%20duty%2C%20there%20was%20just%20one%20problem%3B%20actually%2C%20there%20were%20594%20of%20them.%20Almost%20600%20miles%20separated%20my%20parents'%20home%20in%20coastal%20North%20Carolina%20from%20my%20Brooklyn%20apartment.%20I%20worried%20about%20how%20I%20would%20make%20it%20work%2C%20and%20whether%20my%20job%20would%20make%20accommodations%20for%20me.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20remote%20work%20and%20video%20conferencing%20were%20not%20as%20commonplace%20as%20they%20are%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20employer%20worked%20with%20me%20so%20I%20could%20be%20there%20for%20her%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20much%20discussion%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhr-leaders-recruiters-hiring-managers-manage-stress-burnout-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehuman%20resources%20department%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20keep%20both%20my%20job%20and%20duty%20as%20a%20caregiver.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20I%20had%20been%20living%20in%20New%20York%20for%20eight%20years%2C%20and%20before%20my%20mother's%20diagnosis%2C%20I%20visited%20my%20hometown%20on%20average%20once%20a%20year.%20In%20what%20seemed%20like%20an%20instant%2C%20the%20airport%20terminal%20became%20my%20second%20home.%20Suddenly%2C%20I%20was%20making%20the%20trip%20from%20New%20York%20to%20North%20Carolina%20every%20three%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20visit%20was%20bittersweet.%20There%20was%20the%20joy%20of%20seeing%20my%20mother%2