20Johnson%20was%20an%20immensely%20popular%20political%20leader%2C%20single-handedly%20delivering%20the%20Conservatives%20a%20historic%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFamously%2C%20Johnson%20broke%20down%20part%20of%20Labour%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fpolitics%2F2023%2Fdec%2F11%2Fkeir-starmer-promises-red-wall-voters-the-basics-of-government-done-better%5C%22%3Ered%20wall%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20seats%20%E2%80%93%20historically%20safe%20Labour%20seats%20in%20parts%20of%20Northern%20England.%20With%20Johnson%E2%80%99s%20emphatic%20win%2C%20and%20Brexit%20%E2%80%9Cdone%E2%80%9D%2C%20one%20writer%20predicted%20a%20further%20%E2%80%9Cdecade%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fbooks%2Friding-the-populist-wave%2F4D4C82C02F8A80A03FD2EC18B5D8CACD%5C%22%3Econservative%20dominance%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20the%20decade%20of%20conservative%20dominance%20did%20not%20arrive%2C%20and%20on%20current%20reading%2C%20the%20Conservatives%20look%20destined%20for%20opposition.%20The%20most%20recent%20poll%20confirms%20Labour%E2%80%99s%20long-standing%2020-point%20lead%20over%20the%20Conservatives%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Feurope-poll-of-polls%2Funited-kingdom%2F%5C%22%3E(45%25-25%25)%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Since%20the%20Brexit%20Referendum%2C%20there%20has%20been%20unprecedented%20volatility%20in%20British%20politics%20%E2%80%93%20not%20dissimilar%20to%20the%20leadership%20churn%20in%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%202016%20referendum%2C%20the%20Conservatives%20have%20chewed%20through%20five%20different%20leaders%20from%20David%20Cameron%20to%20Rishi%20Sunak.%20Each%20successive%20leader%20has%20been%20ensnared%20in%20a%20range%20of%20crises%2C%20from%20Theresa%20May%E2%80%99s%20record%20common%20defeats%20over%20Brexit%2C%20Johnson%E2%80%99s%20handling%20of%20COVID%2C%20Sunak%E2%80%99s%20problems%20with%20inflation%2C%20and%20of%20course%2C%20the%20blitzkrieg%20politics%20of%20shock%20and%20incompetence%20of%20Liz%20Truss.%20The%20Conservative%20party%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fbattles-on-the-backbenches-what-are-the-different-factions-in-the-conservative-party-12964275%5C%22%3Efragmented%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20factionalised%2C%20with%20the%20hardline%20right%20pushing%20to%20veto%20key%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22440%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FF81x3f7t07o%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22260%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20volatility%20has%20led%20to%20wider%20governing%20instability.%20Since%202019%2C%20there%20have%20been%20five%20home%20secretaries%2C%20and%20a%20remarkable%20six%20chancellors%20(the%20role%20of%20federal%20treasurer%20in%20Australia).%20This%20turmoil%20takes%20an%20incalculable%20toll%20on%20effective%20government%2C%20as%20policy%20settings%20continuously%20change%2C%20and%20the%20public%20service%20are%20left%20reeling%20in%20the%20aftermath.%20For%20the%20Johnson%20government%20in%20particular%2C%20personal%20loyalty%20and%20factional%20support%20trumped%20appointing%20competent%20ministers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20of%20Priti%20Patel%20is%20instructive.%20She%20was%20forced%20to%20resign%20as%20minister%20for%20international%20development%20in%20the%20May%20government%20in%202017%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fpolitics%2F2017%2Fnov%2F08%2Fpriti-patel-forced-to-resign-over-unofficial-meetings-with-israelis%5C%22%3Eit%20emerged%3C%2Fa%3E%20she%20had%20not%20been%20candid%20about%20unofficial%20meetings%20with%20Israeli%20ministers%2C%20businesspeople%20and%20a%20lobbyist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instituteforgovernment.org.uk%2Farticle%2Fcomment%2Fhandling-priti-patel-bullying-inquiry-has-fatally-undermined-ministerial-code%5C%22%3Ebreaching%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Ministerial%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20for%20allegations%20of%20bullying%20staff%2C%20she%20later%20became%20home%20secretary%20in%20Johnson%E2%80%99s%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20political%20in-fighting%20and%20instability%20in%20the%20Conservative%20party%20fuelled%20volatility%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20has%20led%20to%20voter%20disaffection.%20Suella%20Braverman%20is%20the%20other%20striking%20example%2C%20initially%20appointed%20home%20secretary%20under%20Truss%2C%20she%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fbringing-back-suella-braverman-after-rule-breach-sets-dangerous-precedent-say-mps-12759991%5C%22%3Ebreached%20the%20ministerial%20code%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20sharing%20an%20official%20document%20from%20her%20personal%20email%20address.%20Sunak%20later%20appointed%20her%20home%20secretary%2C%20in%20part%20to%20appease%20the%20hard%20right%20of%20the%20party.%20However%2C%20in%20office%2C%20she%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20political%20liability%2C%20and%20was%20dismissed%20by%20Sunak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22440%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F90OcdXGzSiM%3Fwmode%3Dtransparent%26start%3D0%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22260%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20turbulence%20has%20been%20highly%20damaging%20for%20Sunak.%20Any%20political%20leader%20needs%20clean%20air%20to%20reset%20the%20agenda%2C%20but%20his%20government%20has%20been%20mired.%20He%20aimed%20to%20shape%20his%20agenda%20around%20five%20key%20priorities.%20One%20year%20on%2C%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instituteforgovernment.org.uk%2Fcomment%2Frishi-sunaks-five-pledges-one-year%5C%22%3Ereport%20card%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests%20he%20had%20only%20achieved%20one%20of%20these%20goals%2C%20and%20the%20critical%20ones%20(especially%20on%20immigration)%20are%20%E2%80%9Coff%20track%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImmigration%20is%20the%20political%20battlefield%20the%20Conservatives%20hope%20will%20help%20them%2C%20along%20with%20an%20improving%20economy%2C%20to%20help%20them%20retain%20office.%20The%20resonances%20here%20with%20Australian%20politics%20are%20all%20too%20familiar%2C%20and%20Sunak%20will%20be%20hoping%20for%20a%20repeat%20of%20the%20Liberals%E2%80%99%20emphatic%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allenandunwin.com%2Fbrowse%2Fbook%2FDavid-Marr-and-Marian-Wilkinson-Dark-Victory-9781741144475%2F%5C%22%3Edark%20victory%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%202004%20election.%20However%2C%20Sunak%20is%20widely%20seen%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffingtonpost.co.uk%2Fentry%2Fricher-than-the-king-rishi-sunak-hammered-by-focus-groups-in-swing-english-seats_uk_64c24ed9e4b044bf98f3742f%5C%22%3Eout%20of%20touch%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20wider%20public%20%E2%80%93%20his%20and%20his%20wife%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fpolitics%2F2022%2Foct%2F22%2Frishi-sunak-rich-730m-fortune-prime-minister%5C%22%3Evast%20wealth%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20the%20subject%20of%20much%20commentary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%E2%80%99s%20election%2C%20then%2C%20looks%20increasingly%20like%20one%20Conservatives%20will%20lose%20%E2%80%93%20but%20it%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20how%20well%20Keir%20Starmer%E2%80%99s%20Labour%20can%20win%20it.%20For%20some%20time%2C%20Labour%20has%20held%20a%20solid%2020-point%20lead%20over%20the%20Tories%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.eu%2Feurope-poll-of-polls%2Funited-kingdom%2F%5C%22%3Epolls%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20yet%20to%20take%20office%2C%20Starmer%20will%20need%20a%20record%2012.7%25%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fbritains-labour-would-need-record-vote-swing-win-majority-research-shows-2024-01-16%2F%5C%22%3Eswing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Starmer%E2%80%99s%20team%20will%20take%20inspiration%20from%20Anthony%20Albanese%