ource%3Dweb%26cd%3D%26cad%3Drja%26uact%3D8%26ved%3D2ahUKEwizypyY14mEAxU7TmwGHTNvDu4QFnoECCoQAQ%26url%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fm.economictimes.com%252Fwealth%252Fborrow%252Fwhat-is-pmay-10-important-faqs-about-pradhan-mantri-awaas-yojana-scheme%252Farticleshow%252F76131335.cms%26usg%3DAOvVaw3yFMNQcSGOteFAHf91bA3V%26opi%3D89978449%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Awaas%20Yojana%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fsa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D%26cad%3Drja%26uact%3D8%26ved%3D2ahUKEwi6w5mr14mEAxXvSmwGHc53BXMQFnoECA8QAw%26url%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.kotak.com%252Fen%252Fstories-in-focus%252Floans%252Fhome-loan%252Ffeatures-and-benefits-of-pmay.html%26usg%3DAOvVaw0x6VLLsWS0BN-j4RF7tYBs%26opi%3D89978449%5C%22%3Eprogramme%20aimed%20at%20improving%20access%20to%20affordable%20housing%20for%20the%20poor%2C%20economically%20and%20socially%20backward%20communities%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20country.%20The%20flagship%20programme%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fsa%3Dt%26rct%3Dj%26q%3D%26esrc%3Ds%26source%3Dweb%26cd%3D%26cad%3Drja%26uact%3D8%26ved%3D2ahUKEwizypyY14mEAxU7TmwGHTNvDu4QFnoECCoQAQ%26url%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fm.economictimes.com%252Fwealth%252Fborrow%252Fwhat-is-pmay-10-important-faqs-about-pradhan-mantri-awaas-yojana-scheme%252Farticleshow%252F76131335.cms%26usg%3DAOvVaw3yFMNQcSGOteFAHf91bA3V%26opi%3D89978449%5C%22%3Ewas%20essential%20for%20the%20Modi%20government%20in%20ensuring%3C%2Fa%3E%20cheaper%2C%20affordable%20housing%2C%20which%20tends%20to%20be%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20in%20terms%20of%20asset-ownership%20for%20the%20average%20(poor)%20citizen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98poor%E2%80%99%20in%20extremely%20poor%20states%20may%20have%20voted%20nationally%20in%20the%20past%20for%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20because%20of%20the%20repeated%2C%20time-sensitive%20efforts%20of%20the%20government%20to%20announce%20electorally%20sensitive%2C%20poor-popular%20fiscal%20measures%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fopinion%2F5-year-extension-to-pmgkay-an-acknowledgment-of-indias-nutrition-access-crisis%5C%22%3Eincluding%20the%20extension%20of%20schemes%20like%20PMGKAY%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20larger-electoral%20states%20throughout%20the%20last%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApproaches%20to%20such%20%E2%80%98poor-centred%20welfarism%E2%80%99%20in%20states%20going%20into%20polls%2C%20may%20have%20helped%20the%20BJP%20in%20states%20like%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Chhattisgarh%20and%20Rajasthan%20(more%20recently)%2C%20however%2C%20there%20is%20less%20focus%20on%20welfare%20targeted%20at%20the%20upward%20mobility%20of%20the%20poor%2C%20marginalised%2C%20dispossessed%20sections%20of%20the%20citizenry%20across%20the%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20for%20compromising%20on%20%E2%80%98mobility-centred%20welfarism%E2%80%99%20is%20because%20of%20the%20preference%20attached%20to%20government%20supported%20capital%20expenditure%2C%20which%20in%20this%20interim%20Budget%20too%20saw%20a%2011.1%25%20outlay%20increase%20in%20comparison%20to%20previous%20year.%20As%20argued%20earlier%2C%20in%20studying%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20overall%20macro-outlays%20of%20last%20few%20years%2C%20a%20larger%20proportion%20announced%20for%20capital%20expenditure%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fthree-charts-what-really-matters-to-india-versus-what-parties-jockey-for-in-emotional-tug-to-voters-hearts%5C%22%3Eoften%20come%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20essential%20social%2Fwelfare%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhat-the-interim-union-budget-might-bring-and-the-context-in-which-to-judge-it%5C%22%3Ehas%20otherwise%20failed%20to%20attract%3C%2Fa%3E%20substantive%20private%20investment%20across%20sectors%20which%20has%20made%20the%206%25%20growth%20been%20largely%20driven%20by%20capex-fueled%20government%20spending%2C%20which%20isn%E2%80%99t%20sustainable%20for%20the%20debt%20implications%20it%20has%20on%20the%20government%20and%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20growth%20potential%20(in%20absence%20of%20private%20investment).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20large%20capex-fueled%20government%20spending%20depending%20on%20larger%20borrowings%20has%20already%20made%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fin-9-charts-indias-growing-debt-problem-has-crisis-like-symptoms%5C%22%3Egovernment%20debt%20to%20be%20pegged%20at%20above%2080%25%20of%20GDP%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20not%20meeting%20its%20expected%20revenue%20(or%20disinvestment)%20targets%20year%20on%20year%20to%20meet%20the%20requirements%20imposed%20by%20demand%20for%20greater%20spending%20needs%20(for%20revenue%20and%20capital%20expenditure).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20managing%20its%20own%20fiscal%20deficit%2C%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20this%20Budget%2C%20economic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-economics%2Finterim-budget-2024-six-key-takeaways-9138579%2F%5C%22%3Eanalysts%20expected%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20government%20to%20bring%20down%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20to%205.9%25%20of%20the%20GDP.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-economics%2Finterim-budget-2024-six-key-takeaways-9138579%2F%5C%22%3Efinance%20minister%20did%20slightly%20better%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20announcing%20that%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20has%20been%20brought%20down%20to%205.8%25%20level.%20Further%2C%20the%20finance%20minister%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-economics%2Finterim-budget-2024-six-key-takeaways-9138579%2F%5C%22%3Eannounced%20similarly%20ambitious%20targets%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20FY25%20%E2%80%94%20at%205.1%25%20of%20GDP%E2%80%94%20and%20FY26%20%E2%80%94%20at%204.5%25%20of%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20leads%20to%20two%20questions%3A%20how%20is%20fiscal%20consolidation%20being%20achieved%20(this%20author%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Famid-indias-silent-fiscal-crisis-and-fragile-federalism-16th-finance-commission-has-an-uphill-task%5C%22%3Epreviously%20argued%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20a%20silent%20fiscal%20crisis%20amidst%20high%20debt%20that%20appears%20to%20be%20hidden%20in%20publicly%20accessible%20data)%3B%20and%2C%20even%20if%20one%20agrees%20with%20what%20the%20finance%20minister%20says%2C%20a%20restricted%20fiscal%20space%20%E2%80%93%20just%20to%20meet%20the%20fiscal%20consolidation%20targets%20%E2%80%93%20would%20impose%20adverse%20effects%20on%20growth%20and%20welfare%20performance%2C%20for%20an%20economy%20that%E2%80%99s%20deeply%20affected%20by%20a%20K-shaped%20growth%2Fdevelopment%20pattern.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20managing%20%E2%80%98vanishing%E2%80%99%20middle-class%20expectations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20author%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Farticle%2Feconomy%2Fvanishing-middle-class-struggling-opposition-productivism%3Futm%3Dauthorlistpage%5C%22%3Ehad%20earlier%20discussed%3C%2Fa%3E%20some%20of%20the%20growing%20concerns%20with%20India%20entering%20into%20a%20middle-income%20trap%20while%20witnessing%20a%20deep%2C%20gradual%20erosion%20of%20the%20promise%20of%20upward%20income%20mobility%20for%20its%20broader%20middle-income%20class.%20The%20current%20Budget%20did%20not%20do%20much%20in%20this%20regard.%20The%20finance%20minister%20did%20say%20that%20the%20full%20Budget%20in%20July%20(assuming%20the%20BJP%20will%20comfortably%20be%20back%20in%20power)%20will%20do%20more%20on%20%E2%80%98big-ticket%E2%80%99%20announcements%20keeping%202047%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fthree-charts-what-really-matters-to-india-versus-what-parties-jockey-for-in-emotional-tug-to-voters-hearts%5C%22%3Egrowing%20burdens%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20inflationary%20tax%20in%20a%20period%20of%20stagnating%20real%20wages%20and%20joblessness%20may%20continue%20to%20trouble%20a%20vanishing%20middle%20class%20across%20the%20nation.%20As%20explained%2C%20most%20salaried%20classes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fthree-charts-what-really-matters-to-india-versus-what-parties-jockey-for-in-emotional-tug-to-voters-hearts%5C%22%3Ehaven%E2%80%99t%20seen%20a%20substantive%20rise%20in%20incomes%3C%2Fa%3E%20(across%20both%20urban%20and%20rural%20areas)%20over%20the%20last%20seven%20years%20even%20though%20prices%20of%20essential%20consumer%20and%20capital%20goods%20have%20continued%20to%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fauthor%2F310387%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%5C%22%3Evalue%20of%20the%20rupee%20has%20considerably%20fallen%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20time%20as%20prices%20of%20essentials%20have%20gone%20up%2C%20which%20has%20added%20to%20the%20fiscal%20purse%20of%20the%20average%20Indian%20household%2C%20contributing%20to%20greater%20than%2035%25%20household%20debt%20to%20GDP%20levels%20(see%20more%20on%20this%20issue%20discussed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Farticle%2Feconomy%2Fin-9-charts-indias-growing-debt-problem-has-crisis-like-symptoms%3Futm%3Dauthorlistpage%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20such%20a%20scenario%2C%20for%20those%20coming%20as%20part%20of%20the%20direct%20income%20tax%20base%2C%20providing%20a%20larger%20fiscal%20relief%20could%20have%20been%20desirable%20for%20the%20government.%20The%20previous%20year%E2%80%99s%20Union%20budget%20granted%20income%20tax%20rebates%20for%20individuals%20earning%20up%20to%20Rs%205%2C00%2C000%2C%20creating%20expectations%20among%20the%20lower%20income%20spectrum%2C%20who%20were%20anticipated%20similar%20rebate%20in%20the%20upcoming%20interim%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20look%20at%20some%20of%20the%20other%20key%20macro-overheads%20reflecting%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20fiscal%20outlook.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20capex%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20much%20celebrated%20cornerstone%20of%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20Budget%20presentation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-economics%2Finterim-budget-2024-six-key-takeaways-9138579%2F%5C%22%3Ewas%20the%20spike%20in%20capital%20expenditure%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Modi%20government.%20The%20government%20then%20received%20a%20lot%20of%20praise%20for%20raising%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-economics%2Finterim-budget-2024-six-key-takeaways-9138579%2F%5C%22%3Ecapex%20target%20to%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20the%20data%20for%20revised%20estimates%20now%20shows%20that%20the%20capex%20was%20not%20met%3B%20it%20stands%20at%20Rs%209.5%20lakh%20crore.%20This%20might%20also%20explain%20some%20part%20of%20the%20reduction%20in%20fiscal%20deficit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20even%20more%20troubling%20is%20how%20even%20the%20actual%20spent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fbudget-2023-is-optimistic-but-indifferent-to-past-failures%5C%22%3Ecapex-fueled%20expenditure%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20yielded%20no%20positive%20dividends%20in%20boosting%20domestic%20private%20investment%20across%20sectors%20thus%20far.%20This%20is%20also%20evident%20in%20the%20data%20on%20sectoral%20growth%20(outside%20services)%20and%20its%20contribution%20to%20overall%20GDP%20(see%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhat-the-interim-union-budget-might-bring-and-the-context-in-which-to-judge-it%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20discussion%20on%20this).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20emphasised%20earlier%2C%20it%20is%20a%20collective%20sense%20of%20many%20economists%20by%20now%20that%20an%20increased%20government%20capex%20outlay%20going%20forward%20may%20actually%20do%20very%20little%20to%20change%20the%20underlying%20circumstances%20for%20the%20overall%20private%20investment%20situation%2C%20where%20at%2075%25%20private%20sector%20capacity%20utilisation%2C%20most%20of%20the%20private%20firms%20remain%20reluctant%20to%20invest%20more%20or%20in%20new%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMargins%20for%20companies%20have%20plummeted%20despite%20high%20sales%20growth%2C%20and%20may%20remain%20low%20due%20to%20further%20deceleration%20in%20sales.%20Asset%20utilisation%20rations%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhat-the-interim-union-budget-might-bring-and-the-context-in-which-to-judge-it%5C%22%3Ehave%20remained%20below%20pre-covid%20levels%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20significantly%20lower%20than%20in%20FY12.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20additional%20capex-spending%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fin-9-charts-indias-growing-debt-problem-has-crisis-like-symptoms%5C%22%3Emay%20add%20more%20to%20a%20rising%20government%20debt%20position%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20fiscally%20may%20remain%20hidden%20in%20the%20short%20run%20but%20come%20out%20to%20haunt%20the%20government%20in%20its%20medium%20to%20long%20term%20fiscal%20situation%20later-imposing%20a%20higher%20revenue%20and%20borrowing%20burden%20(see%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fin-9-charts-indias-growing-debt-problem-has-crisis-like-symptoms%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20longer%20discussion%20on%20this).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOn%20revised%20estimates%20and%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20welfare%20spending%20cuts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20fuel%20a%20bloated%20capex-driven%20fiscal%20budget%20and%20fiscally%20afford%20this%20amidst%20weaker%20than%20anticipated%20revenues%2C%20the%20last%20few%20Union%20Budgets%20not%20only%20trimmed%20social%20spending%20but%20did%20so%20in%20a%20year%20when%20capital%20expenditure%20rose%20substantially.%20The%20Modi%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.thewire.in%2Farticle%2Feconomy%2Famid-indias-silent-fiscal-crisis-and-fragile-federalism-16th-finance-commission-has-an-uphill-task%3Futm%3Dauthorlistpage%5C%22%3Ehas%20also%20been%20responsible%20for%20squeezing%20state%20governments%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20inhibiting%20their%20fiscal%20space%20for%20supporting%20welfare%20schemes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20interim%20Union%20Budget%20too%2C%20as%20seen%20in%20the%20past%20where%20health%20and%20education%20budget%20allocations%20are%20typically%20much%20lower%20than%20what%20India%20needs%2C%20the%20revised%20budgetary%20estimates%20now%20show%20that%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-economics%2Finterim-budget-2024-six-key-takeaways-9138579%2F%5C%22%3Ethose%20targets%20from%20past%20budget%20year%20have%20not%20been%20met%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20current%20financial%20year.%20The%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-economics%2Finterim-budget-2024-six-key-takeaways-9138579%2F%5C%22%3Ewas%20supposed%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20spend%20Rs%201%2C16%2C417%20crore%20on%20education%2C%20but%20actually%20ended%20up%20spending%20Rs%201%2C08%2C878%20crore%20(see%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fauthor%2F310387%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20past%20discussion%20series%20on%20how%20less%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20spent%20on%20health%20and%20education%20overall%20in%20the%20last%20ten%20years).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20other%20revised%20estimates%20into%20consideration%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-economics%2Finterim-budget-2024-six-key-takeaways-9138579%2F%5C%22%3Eas%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CSimilar%20cuts%20can%20be%20seen%20now%20in%20the%20budgetary%20allocation%20for%20the%20core%20schemes%20for%20marginalised%20sections%20such%20as%20SCs%2C%20STs%2C%20and%20minorities.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20Revised%20Estimates%20(RE)%20for%20the%20Umbrella%20Scheme%20for%20Development%20of%20Schedule%20Castes%20are%20Rs%206%2C780%20crore%20against%20the%20Budget%20Estimates%20(BE)%20of%20Rs%209%2C409%20crore.%20For%20STs%2C%20the%20RE%20is%20Rs%203%2C286%20crore%20against%20a%20BE%20of%20Rs%204%2C295%20crore.%20For%20minorities%2C%20the%20fall%20has%20been%20the%20sharpest.%20From%20a%20BE%20of%20Rs%20610%20crore%20in%20FY24%20to%20an%20RE%20of%20Rs%20555%20crore.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeeping%20this%20aside%2C%20the%20most%20significant%20reduction%20in%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20own%20social%20spending%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%20was%20further%20observed%20in%20the%20budgeted%20allocation%20for%20the%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act%20(MGNREGA)%20scheme%2C%20seen%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01160433%2FBB1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01160433%2FBB1.png%20650w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01160433%2FBB1-300x202.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-695242%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22438%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20552px)%2085vw%2C%20552px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01160449%2FBB2.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22552%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01160449%2FBB2.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01160449%2FBB2-300x264.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-cont