22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20summer%20of%201978%2C%20the%20historian%20Radha%20Champakalakshmi%20proposed%20to%20the%20Epigraphical%20Society%20of%20India%20that%20the%20Soviet%20Indologist%20Nikita%20Gurov%20be%20invited%20to%20deliver%20a%20special%20lecture%20at%20the%20society%E2%80%99s%20forthcoming%20session.%20She%20was%20member%20of%20the%20society%E2%80%99s%20executive%20committee.%20Some%20senior%20members%20were%20opposed%20to%20the%20proposal.%20Gurov%20was%20acknowledged%20as%20a%20major%20scholar%20of%20Dravidian%20studies%2C%20but%20what%20disturbed%20the%20said%20members%20was%20his%20theory%20that%20the%20Harappan%20script%2C%20which%20has%20remained%20an%20enigma%20a%20century%20after%20it%20came%20to%20light%2C%20was%20in%20fact%20Dravidian.%20They%20were%20willing%20to%20allow%20Gurov%20to%20present%20a%20paper%20at%20the%20session%2C%20but%20a%20special%20lecture%20was%20out%20of%20question.%20All%20the%20same%2C%20they%20knew%20that%20Champakalakshmi%20was%20what%20she%20was%3B%20she%20would%20have%20her%20way%20when%20the%20matter%20came%20up%20for%20discussion%20in%20the%20executive%20committee%20meeting.%20A%20few%20hours%20before%20the%20meeting%2C%20a%20leading%20member%20of%20the%20executive%20committee%20and%20a%20renowned%20historian%20and%20epigraphist%20informed%20her%20in%20person%20that%20the%20meeting%20was%20postponed%20to%20the%20following%20morning.%20The%20next%20morning%2C%20when%20Champakalakshmi%20reached%20the%20venue%2C%20she%20learnt%20that%20the%20committee%20had%20already%20met%20the%20previous%20evening%20as%20originally%20scheduled.%20The%20member%20in%20question%20told%20her%20that%20several%20others%20had%20expressed%20inconvenience%20about%20the%20changed%20schedule%20and%20that%20he%20had%20no%20means%20to%20inform%20her%20of%20this%20last-minute%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChampakalakshmi%20could%20see%20through%20the%20scheme.%20This%20was%20by%20all%20counts%20an%20affront%20to%20her%20dignity%20which%20she%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20take%20lightly.%20She%20decided%20to%20resign%20from%20the%20society.%20A%20mere%20resignation%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20do%2C%20for%20it%20would%20only%20end%20up%20as%20an%20item%20on%20the%20agenda%20of%20the%20next%20meeting%2C%20where%20the%20members%20present%20would%20%E2%80%9Crespect%E2%80%9D%20her%20decision%20and%20approve%20the%20resignation.%20She%20wanted%20to%20let%20all%20members%20%E2%80%93%20some%20250%20at%20the%20time%20%E2%80%93%20know%20why%20she%20had%20resigned.%20She%20drafted%20a%20lengthy%20letter%20addressed%20to%20the%20secretary%2C%20made%20250%20cyclostyle%20copies%2C%20and%20prepared%20the%20envelopes%20for%20dispatch%2C%20writing%20the%20addresses%20on%20all%20envelopes%20in%20her%20own%20hand.%20But%20before%20she%20could%20send%20the%20envelopes%20to%20the%20post%20office%2C%20communication%20came%20from%20the%20administration%20of%20her%20university%20that%20the%20historian%20who%20had%20slighted%20her%20was%20nominated%20as%20external%20examiner%20of%20the%20MPhil%20thesis%20that%20one%20of%20her%20best%20students%20had%20written%20under%20her%20supervision.%20To%20go%20ahead%20with%20her%20decision%2C%20she%20thought%2C%20might%20place%20the%20student%20in%20a%20hazardous%20situation%20(although%20the%20said%20historian%20is%20never%20reported%20to%20have%20harmed%20a%20student%E2%80%99s%20interests).%20She%20placed%20the%20student%E2%80%99s%20career%20before%20her%20self-esteem%2C%20and%20with%20her%20own%20hands%20tore%20into%20bits%20one%20envelope%20after%20another%2C%20transferring%20them%20to%20the%20dustbin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20was%20Champakalakshmi%2C%20the%20human%20being.%20She%20always%20looked%20at%20her%20students%20the%20way%20a%20mother%20looks%20at%20her%20child%3A%20kind%2C%20caring%2C%20ruthless%2C%20exacting.%20It%20was%20not%20for%20nothing%20that%20her%20old%20student%2C%20now%20a%20doyen%20among%20early%20medieval%20historians%20of%20South%20India%2C%20wrote%20on%20his%20Facebook%20wall%20on%20January%2029%2C%202024%3A%20%E2%80%9CRest%20in%20Peace%2C%20my%20mother%20(you%20did%20not%20bear%20me%2C%20though)!%E2%80%9D%20Champakalakshmi%20passed%20away%20the%20previous%20night.%20She%20was%2092.%20She%20was%2C%20even%20so%2C%20as%20intellectually%20incisive%20and%20engaged%20as%20she%20was%20in%20the%20summer%20of%201976.%20With%20her%20demise%2C%20an%20era%20in%20South%20Indian%20historiography%20comes%20to%20an%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChampakalakshmi%20began%20her%20career%20in%20history%20with%20a%20richly%20documented%20study%20of%20the%20Vaishnava%20iconography%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20which%20she%20wrote%20in%20the%20mid-1950s%20as%20a%20doctoral%20dissertation%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Madras.%20She%20was%20already%20redoubtable%20as%20a%20researcher%20at%20the%20time%2C%20encouraging%20her%20supervisor%20T.V.%20Mahalingam%20to%20assign%20her%20and%20a%20fellow%20scholar%20D.%20Devakunjari%20the%20task%20of%20preparing%20the%20index%20for%20his%201955%20book%2C%20%3Cem%3ESouth%20Indian%20Polity%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20was%20the%20final%20word%20on%20the%20history%20of%20south%20Indian%20statecraft%20for%20nearly%20two%20decades%2C%20until%20the%20works%20of%20Y.%20Subbarayalu%20and%20Burton%20Stein%20upset%20the%20apple%20cart.%20Champakalakshmi%20taught%20at%20her%20alma%20mater%20from%201959%20to%201972%2C%20when%20she%20joined%20the%20Centre%20for%20Historical%20Studies%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%2C%20as%20associate%20professor%20of%20ancient%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%2025%20years%20that%20she%20taught%20in%20JNU%2C%20she%20trained%20some%20of%20the%20finest%20historians%20of%20South%20India%2C%20most%20notably%20Vijaya%20Ramaswamy%2C%20Kesavan%20Veluthat%2C%20K.N.%20Ganesh%20and%20Rajan%20Gurukkal.%20She%20was%20demanding%20as%20a%20mentor%2C%20but%20gave%20her%20students%20all%20freedom%20to%20evolve%20academically%20in%20their%20own%20right.%20Veluthat%2C%20Ganesh%20and%20Gurukkal%20went%20with%20Marxism%2C%20an%20intellectual%20tradition%20to%20which%20Champakalakshmi%20was%20deeply%20sympathetic%20but%20didn%E2%80%99t%20embrace%20herself.%20The%20three%20students%20differed%20from%20one%20another%20in%20their%20persuasion%2C%20Veluthat%20endorsing%20political%20determinism%2C%20Ganesh%20social%20determinism%2C%20and%20Gurukkal%20economic%20determinism.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20mentor%20encouraged%20Ramaswamy%20to%20not%20only%20take%20a%20non-Marxist%20position%2C%20but%20also%20make%20a%20powerful%20critique%20of%20an%20important%20Marxist%20position%20in%20Indian%20history-writing%2C%20viz.%2C%20Irfan%20Habib%E2%80%99s%20thesis%20on%20peasant%20unrest%20in%20the%2017th%20and%2018th%20centuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChampakalakshmi%20was%20not%20prolific%20as%20a%20historian.%20Only%20in%201981%20did%20her%20quarter-century-old%20PhD%20thesis%20appear%20as%20a%20monograph.%20This%20work%2C%20which%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20theoretical%20finesse%20noticed%20in%20her%20later%20writings%2C%20continues%20to%20be%20the%20best%20study%20yet%20on%20the%20problem%20it%20examines.%20Her%20major%20contributions%20to%20South%20Indian%20historiography%20were%20in%20the%20form%20of%20research%20papers%2C%20many%20of%20them%20long%20enough%20to%20be%20little%20monographs%20in%20their%20own%20right.%20In%20these%20writings%2C%20she%20came%20out%20as%20a%20Weberian%2C%20foregrounding%20issues%20of%20ideology%20and%20legitimation.%20Weber%20was%20largely%20unknown%20to%20Indian%20historiography%20until%20the%20early%201970s.%20He%20began%20to%20make%20a%20mark%20in%20a%20big%20way%20in%20this%20decade%20when%20in%20their%20writings%2C%20Romila%20Thapar%2C%20Hermann%20Kulke%2C%20M.G.S.%20Narayanan%20and%20Kesavan%20Veluthat%20began%20to%20discuss%20the%20question%20of%20political%20legitimation.%20The%20fascination%20for%20Weber%20came%20partly%20from%20the%20Emergency%20of%201975%20and%20partly%20from%20JNU%E2%80%99s%20active%20participation%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cearly%20state%E2%80%9D%20research%20initiative%20of%20Henry%20J.M.%20Claessen%20and%20Peter%20Skalnik%20in%20which%20legitimation%20was%20a%20major%20theoretical%20concern.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20trailblazing%201978%20paper%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbhakti%20movement%E2%80%9D%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Narayanan%20and%20Veluthat%20had%20confronted%20a%20long%20historiography%20on%20devotional%20conventions%20in%20India%2C%20which%20regarded%20bhakti%20as%20either%20an%20individual%E2%80%99s%20unqualified%20surrender%20to%20the%20divine%20or%20as%20a%20protest%20against%20power%20and%20orthodoxy.%20The%20duo%20argued%2C%20provocatively%2C%20that%20the%20Shaiva%20(Nayanar)%20and%20Vaishnava%20(Alvar)%20bhakti%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%20was%20a%20state-sponsored%20ideological%20initiative%20that%20served%20to%20legitimize%20political%20power%20in%20the%20Pallava%2C%20Chola%2C%20Chera%20and%20Pandya%20realms.%20For%20all%20its%20rough%20edges%20as%20a%20pioneering%20statement%20of%20the%20thesis%2C%20the%20paper%20made%20waves%2C%20and%20was%20widely%20discussed%2C%20endorsed%2C%20restated%20and%20contested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20Champakalakshmi%20who%20developed%20the%20thesis%20in%20empirically%20grounded%20and%20theoretically%20nuanced%20ways.%20She%20picked%20up%20for%20examination%20the%20claim%20which%20Narayanan%20and%20Veluthat%20had%20made%20about%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20geographical%20spread%20of%20bhakti%20by%20plotting%20its%20course%20on%20a%20map.%20She%20argued%20that%20bhakti%20had%20arisen%20as%20a%20protest%20movement%20which%20the%20state%20soon%20appropriated.%20Her%20studies%20on%20economic%20processes%2C%20especially%20trade%20and%20urbanisation%2C%20presented%20temple-centred%20bhakti%20as%20an%20ideology%20that%20determined%20the%20course%20of%20urbanization%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20The%20temple%20was%20the%20great%20legitimiser.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20acts%20of%20validation%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20wrote%20in%20a%20paper%20on%20Kanchipuram%20and%20its%20hinterlands%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmainly%20centred%20round%20the%20temple%2C%20its%20construction%2C%20participation%20in%20gift-giving%20and%20ritual%20activity%20in%20a%20ranked%20hierarchy.%E2%80%9D%20Her%20approach%20to%20architecture%20and%20iconography%20was%20no%20different%3B%20she%20posited%20that%20the%20spread%20of%20Vaishnava%20concepts%20led%20to%20the%20making%20of%20sculptural%20traditions%20among%20the%20Pallavas%20and%20Pandyas%20in%20determinate%20ways.%20Whether%20it%20was%20the%20suggestion%20that%20the%20Tamil%20%3Cem%3ETevaram%3C%2Fem%3E%20texts%20created%20the%20sense%20of%20a%20community%2C%20or%20the%20view%20that%20royal%20trade%20policy%20informed%20the%20patronage%20extended%20to%20religious%20establishments%2C%20her%20later%20writings%20were%20informed%20invariably%20by%20the%20primacy%20of%20ideology%20over%20material%20conditions.%20Most%20of%20her%20papers%20were%20anthologised%20in%20two%20widely%20read%20volumes%2C%20%3Cem%3ETrade%2C%20Ideology%20and%20Urbanization%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1996)%20and%20%3Cem%3EReligion%2C%20Tradition%20and%20Ideology%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2011).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20methodological%20preferences%20made%20Champakalakshmi%E2%80%99s%20studies%20rich%20in%20insights%2C%20especially%20when%20they%20showed%2C%20as%20they%20often%20did%2C%20a%20keen%20eye%20for%20mundane%20historical%20details.%20They%20presented%20a%20gripping%20picture%20of%20the%20making%20southern%20India%20at%20the%20complex%20interface%20of%20power%2C%20religion%2C%20trade%2C%20urbanisation%20and%20an%20expanding%20agrarian%20infrastructure.%20Her%20work%20showed%20that%20a%20theory%20of%20urbanisation%20in%20pre-colonial%20South%20Asia%20was%20perhaps%20incomplete%20without%20a%20corresponding%20theory%20of%20religion%2C%20statecraft%20and%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20the%20love%20for%20the%20ideology-legitimation%20nexus%20often%20led%20her%20to%20look%20for%20ideologies%20where%20they%20might%20not%20have%20existed.%20In%20her%20assessment%20of%20the%20chieftaincies%20of%20the%20Sangam%20era%2C%20she%20regarded%20the%20%3Cem%3Etinai%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20floral%20symbolism%20for%20aspects%20of%20love%20and%20war%20in%20the%20early%20Tamil%20songs%2C%20as%20a%20marker%20of%20geographical%20and%20economic%20reality%2C%20as%20had%20several%20of%20her%20peers%20and%20students%20done.%20She%20went%20a%20step%20ahead%20to%20argue%20that%20two%20of%20the%20five%20%3Cem%3Etinai%3C%2Fem%3Es%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Eneydal%3C%2Fem%3E%20(littorals)%20and%20the%20%3Cem%3Emarudam%3C%2Fem%3E%20(tracts%20of%20settled%20agriculture)%2C%20were%20politically%20decisive%2C%20so%20much%20so%20that%20the%20three%20major%20Sangam%20chieftaincies%20of%20the%20time%20had%20a%20headquarter%20each%20in%20%3Cem%3Eneydal%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Emarudam%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Such%20vanities%20often%20punctuated%20her%20work.%20At%20least%20on%20some%20occasions%2C%20glaring%20inconsistencies%20were%20seen.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20chapter%20in%20%3Cem%3EReligion%2C%20Tradition%20and%20Ideology%3C%2Fem%3E%20identified%20the%20Kalamukha%20Shaivas%20as%20representatives%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20vernacular%20hymnal%20tradition.%E2%80%9D%20The%20preceding%20chapter%20had%20called%20them%20agents%20of%20%E2%80%9CSanskrit%20learning%E2%80%9D%20who%20were%20opposed%20to%20the%20vernacular!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChampakalakshmi%20could%20at%20times%20be%20obstinately%20merciless%20in%20her%20criticism.%20In%20a%20conference%20held%20in%202009%20in%20Kottayam%2C%20where%20the%20who%E2%80%99s%20who%20of%20Indian%20historians%20were%20present%2C%20she%20came%20down%20heavily%20on%20one%20of%20South%20India%E2%80%99s%20groundbreaking%20historians%2C%20asking%20him%20to%20read%20the%20text%20before%20commenting%20on%20it!%20The%20historian%20was%20a%20former%20PhD%20student%20of%20hers%20%E2%80%93%20and%20in%20my%20assessment%2C%20her%20best%20student%20ever%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20paper%20he%20presented%20in%20Kottayam%20was%2C%20in%20my%20judgement%2C%20the%20finest%20that%20was%20ever%20written%20on%20the%20subject.%20Nearly%20everything%20that%20he%20said%20about%20the%20subject%2C%20Sangam%20literature%2C%20was%20new%20and%20carefully%20thought%20out.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20were%20unfair%20to%20him%2C%E2%80%9D%20I%20told%20her%20over%20lunch.%20She%20only%20smiled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20limitations%2C%20copious%20as%20they%20are%2C%20scarcely%20overshadow%20Champakalakshmi%E2%80%99s%20work%20of%20vast%20learning%20and%20erudition.%20For%20her%20writings%20represented%20an%20era%20in%20historiography%2C%20providing%20an%20astounding%20gaze%20of%20historical%20processes%20in%20South%20India%20from%20the%20Sangam%20period%20to%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20Vijayanagara%20state.%20The%20flaws%20will%20soon%20be%20discounted%2C%20and%20the%20appeal%20for%20the%20legitimation%20theory%2C%20already%20on%20the%20decline%20among%20historians%2C%20will%20one%20day%20be%20forgotten.%20The%20work%20will%20remain%2C%20and%20will%20be%20read%20for%20generations%20to%20come.%20Rest%20in%20peace%2C%20Professor%20Champakalakshmi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EManu%20V.%20Devadevan%20is%20Associate%20Professor%20of%20History%20at%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20Mandi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706780743000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01135734%2FScreenshot-2024-02-01-at-1.57.12-PM.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fan-era-called-champakalakshmi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fan-era-called-champakalakshmi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pakistan%20Supreme%20Court%20returns%20Imran%20Khan's%20plea%20challenging%20rejection%20of%20his%20nomination%20papers%20for%20February%208%20polls%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706780545000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22htt