t%20say%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20court%20ruled%20that%20under%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20international%20convention%20on%20terrorism%20financing%2C%20only%20cash%20transfers%20could%20be%20considered%20support%20for%20alleged%20terrorist%20groups.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20ICJ%20opinion%20said%2C%20this%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20not%20include%20the%20means%20used%20to%20commit%20acts%20of%20terrorism%2C%20including%20weapons%20or%20training%20camps.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CConsequently%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20opinion%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20alleged%20supply%20of%20weapons%20to%20various%20armed%20groups%20operating%20in%20Ukraine%E2%80%A6%20fall%20outside%20the%20material%20scope%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20anti-terrorism%20financing%20convention.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EUltimately%2C%20the%20ICJ%20rejected%20most%20of%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20pleas%2C%20finding%20only%20that%20Russia%20was%2C%20%E2%80%9Cfailing%20to%20take%20measures%20to%20investigate%20facts%E2%80%A6%20regarding%20persons%20who%20have%20allegedly%20committed%20an%20offense.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAn%20ICJ%20statement%20said%20the%20court%20%E2%80%9Crejects%20all%20other%20submissions%20made%20by%20the%20Ukraine.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkraine%C2%A0also%20claimed%20Russia%C2%A0violated%20a%20human%20rights%20treaty%20by%20discriminating%20against%20ethnic%20Tatars%20and%20Ukrainians%20in%20Crimea%2C%20the%20peninsula%20that%C2%A0Russia%20illegally%20annexed%20from%20Ukraine%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegarding%20this%20point%2C%20the%20ICJ%20said%20Russia%20had%20violated%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20anti-discrimination%20treaty%20by%20failing%20to%20protect%20Ukrainian-language%20education%20in%20Crimea.%20The%20ICJ%20cited%20